x4freetext: -PRODUCTION OF PROTONS, DEUTERONS AND TRITONS ON CARBON
CYCLOTRON AT THE SWISS INSTITUTE FOR NUCLEAR
.12 CM THICK BERYLLIUM TARGET OR 11 CM THICK CARBON
TARGET, BOMBARDED WITH 590 MEV PROTONS. A PROTON BEAM
INTENSITY OF 120 MICRO-A GAVE A NEUTRON FLUX OF
7.0E+06 NEUTRONS/SEC WITHIN A WELL COLLIMATED BEAM
OF 1 CM2. THE NEUTRONS WERE PRODUCED IN 0.5 NS WIDE
BUNCHES WITH A REPETITION TIME OF 19.75 NS.
.CONTINOUS NEUTRON SPECTRA WITH A DOMINANT 40 MEV WIDE
G/CM2. FOR THE INTENSITY MEASUREMENTS, A 0.583 G/CM2
SHEET OF POLYETHYLENE WAS USED. THE TARGETS WERE SET
INCLINED TO THE BEAM TO MINIMIZE THE ENERGY LOSSES.
THE SAMPLES WERE PLACED AT ABOUT21.5 M FROM THE
THIN (5 MM) NE 102A PLASTIC SCINTILLATORS AND A THIRD
ONE 30 CM IN LENGTH. THE SOLID ANGLES WERE BETWEEN
.AN ADDITIONAL COUNTER ARRAY SET AT 45 DEGREES SERVED
.CORRECTIONS WERE APPLIED FOR TIME DRIFTS AND FOR THE
OVERLAP OF SPECTRA FROM NEIGHBOURING BUNCHES. CORREC-
TIONS WERE ALSO APPLIED FOR AIR BACKGROUND, DEAD-TIME,
